pageContext.claim: “So they apprehended people from the Middle East, and they do it all the time. And everybody says, "Well, where are they from?" We're not talking about only Mexico. All over the world, they come in, because it's a weak spot.”
pageContext.analysis: This is what the briefer told Trump on Jan. 10: "Just yesterday, we apprehended 133 people from countries other than Central America and Mexico. That includes individuals from India, Pakistan, China, Romania, Ecuador, Nicaragua, on and on and on." There was no mention of anyone from a Middle Eastern country.
